Reasoning: 
1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new data structure based on heavy-hitters and inverse maintenance to efficiently implement the interior point method. 
2. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the running time of the algorithm and its optimality among algorithms that do not use fast matrix multiplication. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The interior point method used in the algorithm is inspired by the methods of Lee and Sidford, who have also worked on optimization problems in machine learning. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper proposes a primal-dual interior point method for solving linear programs and discusses the numerical aspects of the algorithm. 
5. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper uses the Johnson-Lindenstrauss lemma, which is a result in discrete mathematics, to efficiently implement the interior point method.
